name: Fushimi Inari-taisha (Unedited Original)
description: In 2016, I took a trip to Japan that was a last ditch effort in many ways. At that point in my life I had conflicted many of my personal relationships, and from within this reckless spiral I jettisoned across the globe in search of reprieve. What I found instead were the stark indicators of flawed foundations and ruined expectations that we, as humans, are often forced to face while coming of age, so to speak.
